<bug>
    <id>101917</id>
    <title>Top-level menu "Alt" accelerators not working</title>
    <description>
        <paragraph id="1">
            <sentence id="1.1">Using Arch Linux, Gnome 3.2.20.</sentence>
            <sentence id="1.2">Pressing either Alt key shows the top-level menu accelerator (e.g. _F_ile, _E_dit, etc.), but pressing the accelerator key ("F" for the File menu, for example) does nothing.</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="2">
            <sentence id="2.1">However, pressing a keyboard shortcut for a second-level menu accelerator (CTRL + "O", for File | Open, for example), *does* work.</sentence>
        </paragraph>
    </description>
</bug>
